channel.title: Help with client version please?
channel.description: idk if this is right topic or not, but how to you find out the client versions? for any server. I know that if you run cmd.exe and type in netstat -o it will give you every server you up connected to via internet

item.title: Help with client version please?
item.dc:creator: @yong_min yong min
item.description:
@yong_min wrote:

Mudclient class -

GameWindowMiddleMan.clientVersion = X;

X will be the client version.

Read full topic

item.title: Help with client version please?
item.dc:creator: @imthenull imthenull
item.description:
@imthenull wrote:

client version has nothing to do with what server you have recently connected to. you can determine the client version by decompiling the client and then looking in the Mudclient class, you can search for version= i believe it is. hope this helps.

Read full topic
